25/11/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The government says it will help 11 Iraqi athletes to qualify for the 2004 Olympics by letting them live and train in the country. 
Romanian experts have picked 11 of Iraq's most promising athletes in five sports -- athletics, canoe-kayak, shooting, judo and weightlifting. 
They will arrive in Romania in January and will train alongside the local Olympic teams until the games.
In other news, centrist opposition parties are demanding they be included in EU accession talks. 
The Liberal Party and the Democratic Party said Monday (24 November) they also want to present their proposals for amendments to the electoral laws. 
(AFP, Mediafax - 24/11/03)
